name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Very beautiful park. Have a great play ground, there is a big wood pirate boat which the kids can have a lot of fun inside, especially the slides are really great. The breach have many families enjoying the breeze, kid‚Äôs building sandcastles

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice, clean park with a dog run as well. A bit further down is the sea with a nice walkway to see the sights with a few chill fishing spots. Calm, relaxed, communal environment

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Located at the extreme north of Singapore lie Sembawang Park and its beach. It is quiet and tranquil here on weekdays. There are people who go fishing, swimming, kayaking, jogging, cycling or just having a family picnic here. There is a public toilet with shower facilities near the beach too. There are many BBQ pits with tables and seats as well. The water at the beach is very clean and clear during high tide and you can see many small fishes at the jetty. You can get there by bus 882 from the bus stop opposite of the Sembawang mrt station.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A nice park by the beach. There are some bbq pits. The toilet has shower. There‚Äôs also a playground for kids. Nice place to catch sunset.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice Park to just walk, a bit small but the different landscape was interesting.  Not easy to get to without car, I think there is a bus that gets here but not sure which one.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place to take a stroll.. but i think the water is still not suitable for swimming. It reeks oil and other pollutants. The park is cleans and give a nice colonial feeling.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
It is a nice and peaceful place full of greenery and a great place to spend the weekends relaxing. They have shelters which is very convenient espcially when raining. You can even stroll on the beaches to look at the beautiful scenery. Nice place to go for a stroll, excercise or jog. They have a place for us to excersise, a playground to play at and BBQ pit for friends and families gathering. The park is very scenic and refreshing.

VERY RECOMMENDED.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Tucked in one corner of north Singapore, beside the sea. Food wise was OK. Typical Chinese food. Acceptable standard. Only setback if makan is at night, walkway poorly lighted. need to be aware of surroundings.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
A relaxing park with a little beach and fishing jetty!

Two washrooms are available there to wash your feet after.

It features a dog park, a playground and a fitness corner near the middle for recreation activities.

There are two carpark (Carpark 1 and 2), Carpark 1 is further to the end and Carpark 2 is at the entrance of the park coming from Sembawang Rd.

Wonderful place to jog around in the morning!

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: There are 2 carparks. Head straight to carpark 1 for easier access to the beach. Carpark 1 is closer to the green spaces. Not advisable to walk barefooted on the beach due to the risk of stepping on glass fragments. The F&B establishment at Beaulieu House doesn't operate all day. According to the signage, it is open from 11am-2.30pm and 5.30-10.30pm.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Pretty clean beach and nice views! Good place to go for a walk. A lot of families/groups set up camp and picnic here though. Would help if there are more dustbins ard bcos of peoples tendency to litter.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Public toilet available.
No food kiosk or food centre anywhere arounds.
Bring your own food. Drinks vending machine only for selected items.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Sembawang Park which is on the northern park of Singapore where it house the colonial house and estate where this place was formerly used by the British military. Weekend is quite crowded and there is a beach area where people can go down to the beach to play. Further to the right of the park you can actually walk into a private estate where you can see those landed house is facing seaside view.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Visited August 2022 in the late afternoon. A large, peaceful park with rolling hills of green, well built paths and recreational areas such as BBQ pits, a huge playground and plenty of benches to sit and enjoy the foliage.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A nice all rounded park. Good for jogging, strolling, big sand playground for children, fitness corner, alot of green spaces for picnic and recently also added a dog park which seems quite well received. There is even a restaurant within the park if you are hungry. I wonder why there isn't more restaurants or eateries there. Coast area is nice during late afternoon time. The only downside is the beach and waters which are not clean.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Little quiet neighborhood park by the beach at the northern end of Singapore.

Ample green space for BBQ and picnic, a walk by the beach and an pretty awesome playground.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Local's secret! This area used to be a naval base and the remaining natural beach. Here u can over see malaysia and the sembawang shipyard. Many come here to chill, swim in the beach, fish , run and theres a dog park , fitnsess gym and playground w sand

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
This is a very nice place to come. Was brought here by a friend and we came by way of cycling.
Soothing and relaxing place, windy and bustling with life.
Nice view to boot too where we can see Johor directly.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: came here on a saturday morning and it was nice and quiet with only a handful of people. after this you can take a bus down to sembawang hot springs, then head further down to chong pang market for food :) worth my $30 cab to come up here from the south!üòÇ

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place to stroll and stretch with lots of fresh air as it is just by the sea. Lots of greenery and not that many people. A great home like restaurant is just a stone throw away from the carpark.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
I was at the Park on 23Oct.
Like to share this info: the Public Toilet 1  ( the one nearer to the beach ) is renovating  from 17Oct22- 31Jan23.
Temporary toilet ( metal wall type )  is provided beside it. About 5 cubicles. Not sure if all have, but some toilet cubicles has shower facilities.
Some distance away, there is Temporary ( portable... plastic type )toilet too.
Hope this info is useful to visitors whom intend to visit the Park !
And hope that visitors and NP Board can maintain good cleanliness of these toilets. Thanks üòä

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Enjoyed the company organized kayaking event there. Nice inner closer to nature place but the downside is without own ride, it's quite a walk to get there after getting off from bus. Thanks for the nice coaches there for guiding us. A shame was that we didn't get to kayak thru the mangrove channel due to low tide, hence missed the chance for that experience.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Popular park on weekends with lots of people on the beach and having BBQs.
Unique feature of the park, it's just next to a shipyard.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Love this place, feel relax here.
Good place to hang out with family, especially kids.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Playground, beach, sheltered area for picnic/bbq and track for cycling or running. There is also a Chinese restaurant located within the park itself.

The beach water was somewhat the dirtiest water in the whole Singapore, not recommended for kids to swim etc. well, plenty of people do fishing activities there or at the jetty though! Good to enjoy the scenery and build some sand castles too.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
It's a nice lil' escape from the buzz around the residential area.

There are many public loos and water fountains around, though perhaps because its a tad isolated than the usual parks, the upkeep on the sanitation side leaves much to be desired.

It's nice that there are outdoor showers, so you can rinse off after some outdoorsy activities or a paddle off the beach.

The beach is a good push off for SUP enthusiasts and for kayaking or canoes. Which is what I did, and we got to venture to the Mangroves about. A nice setting indeed.

I recommend packing an " S " hook with you when you have a planned activity or you won't have anywhere clean or dry to hang your stuff in the loos.

A nice clean park otherwise, and apart from the Sunday dance crowds, it's a nice reprieve.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Don't like other people say there's alot of flower crab not even a single one. I lay 8 crab traps to try it out for 6hours only got stone crab all small size

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Toilets under renovation... but great launching area to Khatib Bongsu mangrove

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Clean and green place which is only for BBQ and gathering. Great place to gather. A great view of the sea too!! ‚ò∫Ô∏è‚ò∫Ô∏è Relaxing...

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Started my Sunday morning at 6am with  walk to Sembawang park. Most of the path is nice with a wide PCN but certain places it is narrow if you are going there from Sembawang or Admiralty . Beach not too clean with some construction going on. But overall it is a nice walk.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: This park is near to our home and we always come here to enjoy the sea view, greenery plus catching some crabs for kids to see. Check on the low tide timing and come here during the low tide sure can see crabs. Kids enjoy it.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Great place for a family outing. Very clean and tidy.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice park w a old building now restaurant

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Very nice park that can get a little crowded on weekends. The view is very good and neighboring Malaysia can be seen from here. There is also a beach with sand so children can play here as well. Barbecue pits are available and it is quite windy during the evenings so it is suitable for a picnic. At night, the park is not well-lit. There are only a few toilets in this park, however.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Sunset is blocked at this time of the year but still enjoy the lush greenery and open space.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A place to find your missing husband or wife in this secluded park, especially at the first car park Tuah Rd. Many cars, van parked here at night with engine running.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
One of the oldest park in Singapore, however of late NEA upgraded and renovation gave this park a renewal fresh feel.
Post renovation works (between 2020 till 2022) have vastly improved this beautiful and matured park in the north that allows families and people to get together to chill and enjoy or exercise and workout.
Good place to visit to get close to mother nature.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Beautiful calm place.. lovely environment and parks. Great place yo stay. MRT and Bus connectivity is good. From station to Sembawang Park you can take bus no . 882. It's the last stop.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
It's a nice small, quick to go family beach and park. The park is big with lavish green grass and few barbecue pits. Many shelters.

It's good for family outing. Don't have high expectations on the beach.

Sometimes there are mosquitos and good to keep a repellent all time. Suddenly rains and also have a umbrella handy.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
For those who is living in northern part of Singapore, Sembawang Park is the perfect place to bring my family to a picnic by the beach.

Bring along your food, floor mat, spare cloths, & sand castle to make it a picnic to be remembered. If you are taking public transport, you can reach Sembawang park via bus service 882 from Sembawang interchange..

If you are hungry, do drop by the food stalls located near the junction of Sembawang Road & Admiralty Road West..

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice park for family to come with children and their pets for scooting, riding bicycles, playground and seaside sand fun. The beach is relatively small and get crowded on weekends. Nonetheless it is still a great place to come with young children to have a fun sandy time, and there‚Äôs a toilet nearby to wash up too, but it‚Äôs definitely not for fussy children or adults.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: An old park with Sembawang Beach at the far end. Make it a part of your heritage trail to see black and white bungalows, WWII bunkers and historical buildings within that area.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
I promise I will not be biased about loving Sembawang park just because I live really close to it. Sembawang park is serene, tranquil and peaceful. It's a hidden gem in Singapore. You can complete the trail in the park in 30 minutes with jogging, 45minutes with quick walk, or 80minutes with a slow walk. I personally think this park is simply the best, great for age 0-99 it's a park that you will not get lost in.
The reason for its one star short is because of the cleanliness of the beach.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: True to its history, the park has ties to its naval park with the battleship scaffold inspired playground, its close to the shipyard, Beaulieu house (neoclassical British era heritage building) and a beach (one of the last natural ones). The sunrise is a definite must do! There is even a dedicated dog park. A lot of birds and interesting trees to explore. There is a jetty filled with people fishing as well as enjoying the sea breeze. It‚Äôs a great place for picnic and family get-together and convenient to arrive by public transport.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice park, playground, beachfront, dog run..

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Was lucky to see this view on a Saturday. Clear water and no crowd.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
My weekend exercise playground.
Nice seaview and sunrise.
Try digging for some seashells during low tide.
There are 2 carparks available which I NEVER have to worry about no parking. Parking is free by the way.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Beautiful park that's been around for decades. Lovely old trees, really cool playground for kids and even a small beach to relax around. I wouldn't swim in it though, water looked brackish. Beaulieu House still stands with a very quaint western and Chinese menu.

4 stars because beach is closed till Sep 21 for maintenance and too many anglers taking up space. Also spotted several people smoking despite being a smoke free park üò©.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Great location, good parking, clean,
Bus access...great sunrise and sunsets

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Decided to come here on a late Sunday evening. There were quite a lot of people having picnic here. Quite happening. There is a huge battleship style playground. Looks interesting. Very nice that they have public toilets here (with toilet paper!). The jetty of full of people fishing. Then there were also a group of ladies scouring the rocky area, seemingly to harvest some shellfish. Too far though, couldn't see what they were. Next time would come here on a non-peak timing hopefully there is less people.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Its a good park, neat and clean. Kids have enough space to play. Few BBQ pits also available with lots of seats. Only problem i found was the restrooms near by bbq pit is under renovation. If it is ready, its a good place.
And one another thing is its just few meters away from beach also. But beach area is not clean.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Good place for a nice afternoon or evening stroll amidst the greeny of the park and  straits of Johor view. Even though not too tranquil due to the activities of nearby shipyard, the place is rich with flora and fauna. You can see parrots and small crabs.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Good place to breathe fresh clean air

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Surprisingly it was good! As I have a post-Aussie feels and thinking Singapore might not have any nature places near to the sea or places with less crowded, then I found this place nearby my stay, I‚Äôm happy I found this . I hate crowds üòÇ

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Good hangout spot during the day
Rather dim in the night.
Beach are clean too.
There's a restaurant in a colonial house.
The jetty is a popular spot at night.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Quiet and not so crowded. Just quite some trash being washed up the beach.. but otherwise should be nice place to visit

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place to spend evening time. Specially enjoy the entry into the beach through the park. You can also observe Malaysia boarder and Johor Bahru other side. You can see large ships just beside the park. Paddling also available.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Sembawang Park is a tranquil lush park along the Straits of Johore. There are lot of trees, birds, flowers, shelters, dog run, playgrounds, toilet facilities and a small stretch of sandy beach. The playground has a ship like shaped structure on sand for parents with small children to play. They will certainly enjoy it. Next door is Sembawang Shipyard which was called H M Dockyard during the British administration. The ship shape structure is a good reminder. It is also good place to do your Yoga, breathing in the smell of salt in the atmosphere. There is also a fishing jetty for anglers to enjoy their sports. You could also pitch a tent, permit needed from NPark and have a picnic with your family but not now because of Covid. You also have a panoramic view of the Johore landscape. Enjoy the amenities at the park, keep the place clean and move in pairs as the Covid 19 rule is still in force.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: I live near by but apart from visiting the eateries near by,  I had never really explore the park. Till the day I visited. Arrived around 0700hrs and was enjoying the light breeze and sounds of the waves hitting the beach when suddenly I saw the sunrise! I saw it rise up and was filled with hope of a new day and warmth. I am breathing and with that I am thankful!

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Relaxing not too crowded even though it is New Year's Eve. Is good for family outing, there are toilets with shower facility where children can clean up after playing at the beach.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Medium sized park in the northern part of Singapore. In the park near the beach area is a historical building that is repurposed as restaurant in present day. Exercise area (with pull up bars), jetty for fishing, BBQ pits, dog run, playground are available. Visitors could take a stroll along the beach line towards east direction park connector to the landed property area and that would make a good 6-7km jogging track.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: It been quite awhile since I last visited the park at night. Saturday still seem quite popular which people fishing or catching  crabs ü¶Ä. No windy but still OK.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Sembawang Park is a small park facing JB, and next to the dry dock in Sembawang. It doesn't look great at the jetty area there although still full of people.
There is a restaurant in a historical building near the sea side which is a beautiful building.

However, the inner part of the park is great with a big piece of grass for people to outing. It's a nice park as long as you drive as it's a bit far from the MRT station.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
A place to past time.
Do bring your own drinks and food.
Getting there is quite easy with bus service 882 opposite Sembawang MRT station. There's a carpark for those who drive.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
If you are looking for a place for picnic away from the crowd, this park will be ideal. Good place for exercise, especially early morning, I go almost every weekend there. Also place for Chill Out at the Seaside, can enjoy the gentle sea breeze and sound of the waves even though not suitable for swimming.
It has few Barbecue facilities so can spend good time with family during weekend :)

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place to chill n do fishing.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Small park beside a shipyard, there's a restaurant (beaulieu house) by the beach too! Woody Family Cafe is also about a 5mins walk from the entrance of Sembawang park. There is a dedicated place for dogs to freely run about too!

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Calm and breeze. People can get relaxed.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Love it totally for it completeness.  Areas for dogs only; kids play area and adult seating area . Sufficient public toilets and even a restaurant which is see facing. Serene park for all..

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: You can get a nice sunrise view at the beach, besides doing morning exercise and many were here for fishing too

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice and peaceful place to relax on weekday

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
The tranquility of the nature balances immensely the calming waters in this secluded park. Sunrises during morning runs are always a pure enjoyment and such appreciation of its beauty will always leave people in awe.

Be sure to walk up to the jetty to see what local fishing enthusiasts caught on their fishing reel. The Beaulieu House sits in the main area of the park that used to be a old colonial residence for the British before its current makeover to a restaurant that serves local delights.

The park is clean and nice, with good toilets accessibilities and showering facilities. Various water coolers are conveniently located within the park as well.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Not bad for a public park. There is a jetty where some gather to fish and your can see a dry dock there. A marvelous playground that are garanteed to make the kids crazy with joy. A interesting restaurant are also on site which are will received.

Go in the day time if you want sun burn. The night was much kinder.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
A fairly large park with a decent amount of beach area. Certain parts of the park do get a bit spooky and quiet on weekdays, but on weekends, it's bustling with activities.

There's several BBQ pits that can be booked. Also, there's a large field that's popular with people playing frisbee and cricket and letting their dogs run around. There's also a few playgrounds and fitness corners.

You get a clear view of Johor, Malaysia from the beach. The park is served with two bustops. Bus service 882.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: What a nice park! great walking trails, water views, bathrooms,  kids playing area, and workout area.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Tucked in the northern end of Singapore, be prepared to sit at the beach facing Johor Bahru (Permas Jaya, Masai & Pasir Gudang) enjoying the cool breeze and the lack of patrons. The beach is situated after a park, which is well connected via tarred footpaths.

I didn't know of this Gem until a friend told me about it. Otherwise, the only beach I would have known would be East Coast Park beach. Lol. You gotta come here and feel at peace with nature, knowing there will not be many people loitering about and you could find some tranquillity and quiet if you were to visit this place.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A fantastic park for the family to walk and exercise. Plenty of space and track avail for a jog. The surrounding nature is full of the lustre greens and trees. Game for a family fun and create your own outing? üòé

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Clean and quite Park. Seeing ppl fishing boating. Jetty is allowing you to walk down for viewing. A restaurant, playground, rest shelter, public toilet was there. Have to brings water along as no vending machine around.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice beach and big park for a walk or exercise. There is a dog runner corner too. A restaurant on the hill but pricey.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: I just love the view from the cottage,nice scener,fresh air,relaxing.....it's a nice place to gather and have fun with friends during off daysüòäAnd if you love  cooking barbecue food,you can book a barbecue pit in there as well... üòäüòäüòäüëç

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Overall a tranquil place to chill with family and friends over the weekends. Take a stroll with your lover on the beach or pick a spot for a picnic/bbq. There's also a playground to entertain the kiddos. Nothing impressive but good enough for a short family outing or take a breather from everyday stress.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Masha allah..  Very nice place

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
A very beautiful park and beach filled with greenery, a huge dog run field, BBQ pits, fishing and water sports activities. many social activities are carried out there and public is welcome to join.

For food, there is Beaulieu House is a Seaside Restaurant managed by Sembawang Seafood Paradise Pte Ltd serving Western cuisine, Chinese seafood and local delights.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: My husband and I enjoyed our walk very much at this quiet and lovely park. It was not that far from city as we imagined. Will visit the restaurant soon.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Nice breezy sea view park that look over to Malaysia.

A small beach area

There are bbq pits for rent.

Jetty for fishing

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Very calm and peaceful. The beach was not too crowded. Taking 882 bus from Sun Plaza was straightforward. A lot of people came for fishing and picnic.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A combination of park, shipyard and mini-beach. This is the only beach for people staying in the north to enjoy beach therapy without traveling all the way to the east. You might be able to watch large vessel ship cruising off or docking in close-up view. Wrapped up the day by getting a ice cream from the ice cream vendor at the bus-stop and melt into the sunset with a dose of Vitamin sea.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Great place to see the sun and the sea. There is even a small stretch of beach! Great for kids as there is the special Ship Playground, and a good place to jog and exercise, but might get crowded too.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A nice park in the North West of Singapore. There is a small beach but still cannot be compared with the East of Singapore beaches.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Lovley black & white houses. Close to the harbour.  Perfect view

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Directly opposite Johor! Spacious and Windy! Great for family gathering.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place for family with kids to play around leisurely

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: A small relaxing park with interesting landmarks like a tiny but buzzing jetty, a restaurant in colonial style building and a battleship playground. Good rest stop for cyclists too.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: The best time on the beach is during low tide, as higher tide means there is only a small strip of sand on the beach.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Situated in the north of Singapore facing the Johor Straits, ‰∏âÂ∑¥Êó∫ÂÖ¨Âõ≠Ôºåit is a wonderful place for jogger, for people who like the Clean sandy beach,  small jetty and can accomodate very little anglers,
But it is still a good place for family gathering & time to relax with splendid outdoor activities.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Great place for barbeque, picnic, walk and run. The big playground currently is under renovation. No camping is allow. Sembawang shipyard is just opposite the jetty. May take bus 882 from Sembawang Interchange.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Was there to enjoy with family including toddlers. Beach is not huge so best to go when it's less crowded. Might not be one of the best place to swim cause of dark water. Part of beach area was under construction. Jetty can be used for fishing. Changing/Shower was close to beach. There was a huge playground for kids. Easily accessible by bus 882 from Sembawang MRT/Interchange. Recommended for northie folks.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Quiet n peaceful beach in e morningüå¥üåûnot that crowded with big green field

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: This place is nice for exercise, picnic with family n good for fishing too but some places are closed under contractions.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Nice place when you are want to see sunset here üåÖüåÖüåÖ
kids are happy for spend time at here also‚è≥‚è≥‚è≥

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice place for walks and plenty of shelters to rest and relax.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Sembawang Park is quite a big park by Singapore standard but walking is easy even for seniors like me (75) as the ground is quite flat. The tall trees provide excellent shade. There are two car parks and they're free for park visitors. There are play grounds for the young and cycling is allowed. BB pits are closed üò¢ due to the COVID-19. Seats are dotted throughout the park with two modern toilets üöª for visitors. There's a small beach and a short jetty. My wife and I love the beautiful Beaulieu House üè†, now an operating restaurant. Recommended for the young and old and best in the morning and evening.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Beautiful sunrise and evening view, take a slow walk along the beach you will discover surprise.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Great place to have workout there, love the beach n nice food at Beulieu Houseüëç

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Beautiful open area.We can do camping there in a peaceful place. Pls keep the beach cleaning so that we all can enjoy the nature's beauty in a clean place and be thoughtful to ecosystem as well.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Possible to take bus 882 in! Do not walk in. Google sometimes doesnt show that there is a bus 882! Lol.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Beautiful place for sunrise photos and toilets are clean. A great place for picnic too !

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice park with small beach.Pretty clean beach and nice view.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text: Nice Park and Environment to Cycle and have Fun . Would be nice if there was a Vegetarian Restaurant here to Cater to The needs of Vegetarians and Promote Kindness towards wildlife and Our Environment .

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Small but beautiful park to have a quiet peaceful walk. We went on a Sunday morning and the place was not crowded. There were few groups of people dancing and exercising and a few people walking their dogs like us.

BBQ pits are also available for rent and are placed conveniently near the public toilets.

Beach offers a nice view of Malaysia but wouldn't recommend to take a soak in the water as the place is very near a shipyard.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Facing the Straits of Johor, Malaysia, the Sembawang Park is a 15-hectare park situated in the north side of Singapore. The best part about the park is that it actually has a clean and sandy beach where kids can build sandcastle on. I personally found the sound of the waves to be very therapeutic, peaceful and calming. In all, this is a good place for brisk walking, jogging, cycling, BBQ-ing, fishing, group exercising, relaxing and having picnics.

Tips:
1) Bus service 882 can take you from Sembawang Bus Interchange to the front and end of Sembawang Park.
2) There are free fitness classes sponsored by the Health Promotion Board on every Sunday. Google Sundays at the Park (SATP) to find out more!

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Sembawang Park is a great oceanside park. Entering the park, a slight breeze rustles the leaves making them fall to the solid ground one by one. Slowly the wind picks up as time passes and soon there are strong gusts of wind from the sea breeze. Sitting at the corner of the park you can also spot the harbour and many ships as they pass by and the sunsets in the background. In the past itself, there are families having barbecues while children run around and play at the playground. Squeals of laughter come from there.

The leaves rustle as night falls and crickets and bullfrogs come out. Soon there are loud insect sounds and dim lights that keep the atmosphere nice and warm. There is also a restaurant nearby which you can go to if your craving some Chinese or even western food, the food there is also to die for. It is also not too crowded, so its a great place if you want some peace and quiet, away from the hustle and bustle of Singapore, especially after work is it is a great place to just enjoy the cool, gentle breeze, and nice atmosphere.

Would definitely come here again, it is really great and nice place to hang out with friends or even family.

name: Sembawang Park
review_text:
Sometimes, timing is everything.

Imagine stepping into the park, hoping for some respite from the mid-day sun, and immediately experiencing a stiff sea breeze  followed by a gentle cascade of yellowing leaves from the surrounding trees.

For a few fleeting moments, it felt like a late summer / early autumn day in a temperate country instead of equatorial Singapore. Sembawang Park isn't the most accessible green space around but maybe that's why it is so charming.

From the unique battleship-themed children's playground to the little sandy strip of beach overlooking Johor Bahru, to the cluster of abandoned 1920s colonial bungalows at the park's fringes, this lesser-known park has a bit of something for nature and history buffs alike.

there. Not a place that is easily accessible by public
transport.

This park is not big but there is ample greenery. There are
some low-rise housing nearby and if you walk further in, you reach a

Malaysia. Along the beach, you should be able to see few ships
